<BYLINE>By LARRY McSHANE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 It's been 31 years since `` Dem Bums'' became beach bums, since <PERSON> Walter </PERSON> <PERSON> O'Malley </PERSON> moved the <ORGANIZATION> Brooklyn </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Dodgers </ORGANIZATION> to <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION>. The wounds have yet to heal. Today, the <ORGANIZATION> Dodgers </ORGANIZATION> return _ to <LOCATION> Shea </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Stadium </LOCATION>, not <LOCATION> Ebbets </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Field </LOCATION> _ to play the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mets </ORGANIZATION> for the National League pennant. But to many Brooklynites, this homecoming to the borough of <LOCATION> Queens </LOCATION> will be happy only if the <ORGANIZATION> Dodgers </ORGANIZATION> go down in defeat. `` The old <ORGANIZATION> Brooklyn </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Dodgers </ORGANIZATION> were a very special team, in a very special time, in a very special place. The <ORGANIZATION> Los </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Angeles </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Dodgers </ORGANIZATION> are not really the <ORGANIZATION> Dodgers </ORGANIZATION>,'' said <PERSON> Brooklynite </PERSON> <PERSON> Frances </PERSON> <PERSON> Macrillo </PERSON>. `` They do n't look like the <ORGANIZATION> Dodgers </ORGANIZATION>, they do n't sound like the <ORGANIZATION> Dodgers </ORGANIZATION>,'' she continued. `` It's very easy to root for the <ORGANIZATION> Mets </ORGANIZATION>.'' Ms. <PERSON> Macrillo </PERSON>'s cheers are echoed by the many <LOCATION> Brooklyn </LOCATION> fans who swore off the <ORGANIZATION> Dodgers </ORGANIZATION> on Oct. 23, 1957, when <PERSON> O'Malley </PERSON> moved the team of <PERSON> Jackie </PERSON> <PERSON> Robinson </PERSON>, Pee Wee <PERSON> Reese </PERSON> and <PERSON> Duke </PERSON> <PERSON> Snider </PERSON> closer to <LOCATION> Catalina </LOCATION> than <LOCATION> Coney </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Island </LOCATION>. Boxing publicist <PERSON> Irving </PERSON> <PERSON>