RGANIZATION> Dodgers </ORGANIZATION> to the playoffs with a vitriolic column in which <PERSON> O'Malley </PERSON>'s name was preceded each time with an epithet. `` Some wounds never heal,'' wrote <PERSON> Hamill </PERSON>, who broke a three-decade boycott of <ORGANIZATION> Dodgers </ORGANIZATION> home games this week to root for the <ORGANIZATION> Mets </ORGANIZATION> -LRB- who, by the way, have eight native Californians on the roster -RRB-. `` I go to the enemy camp'' _ <LOCATION> Dodgers </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Stadium </LOCATION>, that is _ `` as a hostile witness,'' he wrote. `` And the vow still holds. Never forgive. Never, ever forget.''
