<HEAD>Residents Brace For Spraying Against Medflies</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Leads with 3 grafs to UPDATE with spraying under way; picks
up 3rd graf: `The National ...</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By RICHARD DE ATLEY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Three pesticide-laden helicopters took off on an aerial spraying mission Thursday night to fight the Medfly infestation that has set up a base in <LOCATION> Beverly </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hills </LOCATION> and the city's toney <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Side </LOCATION> `` They're currently over <LOCATION> Beverly </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hills </LOCATION>,'' said <PERSON> Tom </PERSON> <PERSON> Kenney </PERSON>, a <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Aviation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Administration </ORGANIZATION> controller at <LOCATION> Santa </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Monica </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Airport </LOCATION> where the choppers departed from shortly after 8 p.m. The spraying program is the first step in an all-out attack against the Mediterranean fruit fly, a pest that destroys about 250 varieties of produce. The <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Weather </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> again forecast coastal fog for the area Thursday night, but officials moved the starting time up 2 -LCB- hours to 8 p.m. hoping to beat the rolling fog bank. The spraying was ordered because 47 Medflies were found in yards since Sept. 26, a serious infestation that if allowed to spread would threaten fruits and vegetables that are a major part of <LOCATION> California </LOCATION>'s $ 15.5 billion-a-year farm economy. The Thursday flight was set for a 35-square-mile area of 100,000 residents that includes middle-class stucco homes, mansions, swank Rodeo Drive shops and luxury car dealerships, all subject to the honey-like stickiness of the Malathion spray. Along with parts of <LOCATION> Beverly </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hills </LOCATION>, officials are spraying sections of western <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> and the adjacent cities of <LOCATION> Culver </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hollywood </LOCATION>. At <PERSON> Martin </PERSON> <PERSON> Cadillac </PERSON> on the corner of <LOCATION> Olympic </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Boulevard </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Bundy </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Drive </LOCATION> in <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION>, a caravan of about 100 shiny Caddies left the sales lot Wednesday night for an underground parking lot at a bank building six blocks away, sales manager <PERSON> Steve </PERSON> <PERSON> Mitchell </PERSON> said Thursday. He said several of the cars were returned to the sales lot Thursday morning for potential tire-kickers, with the luxury car exodus to be repeated at nightfall. The pesticide poses no health risks, health officials say, but the sticky corn syrup bait mixed with the Malathion could mess up a car's paint job. Museums in the area covered their outdoor statues. Agricultural Commissioner <PERSON> Leon </PERSON> <PERSON> Spaugy </PERSON> said the fight to save the state's farm industry knows no economic boundaries. `` We're encouraging people to cover up their Rolls Royces just like they would cover up their Pintos,'' he said on Wednesday
