orida </LOCATION> in their hopes of regaining a majority in the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION>. A strong showing by Republican presidential nominee <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>, who is expected to win the state, could also hurt <PERSON> MacKay </PERSON>. And then there is the money factor. <PERSON> Mack </PERSON>'s campaign has raised more than $ 4 million, including $ 860,000 from the <ORGANIZATION> GOP </ORGANIZATION>'s national <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> campaign committee, and spent about $ 3.5 million to maintain his media effort. <PERSON> MacKay </PERSON> raised and spent $ 1.5 million he needed to reach the general election. The national <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION> is expected to give <PERSON> MacKay </PERSON> $ 700,000.
