's pink shoe and to cut open the white boots. There was no blood found inside the shoe and we conclude that the shoe could not have been worn when cut. ... The feces found on the pink blouse and shoe Ms. <PERSON> Brawley </PERSON> was wearing when found, -LRB- and -RRB- on the gloves found in the bag in which she was discovered ... contained dog hairs which were consistent with the hairs from a dog owned by the occupant of Apartment 21A.'' _ `` There is no medical or forensic evidence that a sexual assault was committed on <PERSON> Tawana </PERSON> <PERSON> Brawley </PERSON>. If a 15-year-old girl has been forcibly raped or sodomized by multiple assailants over a four-day period, there is a high probability that medical or forensic evidence would have been found.'' _ `` When discovered, <PERSON> Tawana </PERSON> <PERSON> Brawley </PERSON> was not suffering from exposure. If an individual had been outdoors continuously from Tuesday evening, Nov. 24, to Saturday afternoon, Nov. 28, when the temperature several times dropped to the freezing point, there is a high probability the individual would have suffered from exposure. ... When discovered, <PERSON> Tawana </PERSON> <PERSON> Brawley </PERSON> was not malnourished. ...''
