 been fluctuating,'' he added. Oct. 10 is a national holiday for both <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION> and the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>. For <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION> it is Health-Sports Day, while the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> celebrates Columbus Day. Both stock and foreign exchange markets in <LOCATION> Tokyo </LOCATION> are closed on the second Saturday every month.
