 <ORGANIZATION> Bic </ORGANIZATION> is recalling its new, regular size fixed-flame cigarette lighters because some of them may fail to extinguish, the <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Consumer </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Product </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Safety </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION> announced today. About 6.5 million of the lighters have been distributed since they were introduced in July, the agency said. No incidents or injuries have been reported involving the lighters. But the company decided on the recall after determining that the fire may not go out on 0.04 percent of the lighters, the commission reported. The problem has been corrected on lighters now being made, officials said. The lighters in question are sold in a plastic pouch or tray and are labeled `` with fixed flame.'' They can be identified because they do not have the small wheel used on some lighters to adjust the flame size. Bic Mini fixed flame lighters and <ORGANIZATION> Bic </ORGANIZATION> regular sized adjustable lighters, which represent 98 percent of <ORGANIZATION> Bic </ORGANIZATION> lighters on the market, are not involved in the recall, the commission said. Consumers should stop use of the regular size fixed flame lighters and return them to the store where purchased for a refund. Those needing more information can contact the commission at 1-800-638-2772.
