oubt their hardships are severe _ when it comes to the plights of the victims and their families, there is what one can only describe as an astounding lack of sensitivity, a lack of human compassion. <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> said, `` I hope I'm wrong about this but I do n't think so, in the year since it happened, the governor of <LOCATION> Massachusetts </LOCATION> has never aplogized to the Barnes for their ordeal In <PERSON> Medina </PERSON>, <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> said the federal government does not furlough murderers who have not served enough time to be eligible for a parole. Even so, <PERSON> Craig </PERSON> <PERSON> Fuller </PERSON>, <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>'s chief of staff, said the vice president feels the federal furlough program `` should be reviewed'' for possible changes. <PERSON> Fuller </PERSON> said <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> was satisfied it was `` fundamentally different'' than the former Massachussetts program.
