rney for <PERSON> Sturgis </PERSON> said he pulled the gun because of a `` startle reflex.'' He said the judge had been the victim of an attack and was nervous about courthouse security. The last judge ordered to appear before the court for reprimand was Circuit Judge <PERSON> Jack </PERSON> <PERSON> Block </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Miami </LOCATION>, who was rebuked two years ago for violating legal ethics before he joined the bench, said <PERSON> Sid </PERSON> <PERSON> White </PERSON>, clerk of the court. Usually, the court issues reprimands in writing.
