 The British government's demand that <LOCATION> Kuwait </LOCATION> halve its stake in <ORGANIZATION> British </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Petroleum </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>. PLC has drawn fire from critics who fear it may discourage foreign investment in the already depressed <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> stock market The government said Thursday it acted to defend the free market against a cartel, the <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Petroleum </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exporting </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Countries </ORGANIZATION>, to which <LOCATION> Kuwait </LOCATION> belongs. British Petroleum is <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION>'s largest company, and the <LOCATION> Persian </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Gulf </LOCATION> nation of <LOCATION> Kuwait </LOCATION> is its biggest shareholder.
