<NOTE>Eds: ADDs 6 new grafs after 5th graf pvs with new information;
picks up 6th graf pvs, ``Smith made ..''</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By TONY KENNEDY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>MINNEAPOLIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 While <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> has not rejected <ORGANIZATION> Grand </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Metropolitan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> PLC </ORGANIZATION>'s $ 5.2 billion takeover offer, it has become increasingly hostile toward the British company, warning shareholders not to be fooled by its `` blitz campaign.'' In his first major public response to the unsolicited $ 60-a-share bid launched Tuesday, <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> Philip </PERSON> <PERSON> Smith </PERSON> <PERSON> Grand </PERSON> <PERSON> Met </PERSON> was trying to `` stampede'' shareholders and others into believing the offer was `` good for all our constituents.'' `` We should not accept Grand Met's words at face value,'' he said Thursday. <PERSON> Smith </PERSON> also told <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION> employees to treat the British food and liquor conglomerate with skepticism when it claims that a successful takeover would not result in major job cuts. Separately, <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION> said late Thursday that a <LOCATION> Michigan </LOCATION> state judge had upheld a restraining order barring Grand Metropolitan from buying any <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION> stock because of questions over whether a buyout would violate liquor laws in a number of states. <PERSON> Smith </PERSON> and two other <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION> officials met privately late in the day with Gov. <PERSON> Rudy </PERSON> <PERSON> Perpich </PERSON> at the Capitol to brief the governor on the takeover `` in terms of <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION>'s perspective,'' <PERSON> Ray </PERSON> <PERSON> Bohn </PERSON>, <PERSON> Perpich </PERSON>'s communications director, confirmed today. <PERSON> Bohn </PERSON> said the <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION> officials requested the meeting and spent between 30 and 45 minutes with the governor. `` They know that, in terms of legisla