ry </ORGANIZATION>, but `` Grand Met's history is filled with just the opposite kind of corporate behavior,'' <PERSON> Smith </PERSON> said in his letter, which did not cite examples. <PERSON> Walter </PERSON> <PERSON> Montgomery </PERSON>, a spokesman for Grand Met in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, disputed <PERSON> Smith </PERSON>'s remark about job reductions. `` The letter is what it is,'' <PERSON> Montgomery </PERSON> said. `` It has a purpose. You figure it out.'' <PERSON> Smith </PERSON> also disputed assertions by security analysts, Grand Met and some newspapers that <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION> has few choices in dealing with the takeover bid. `` ... They have no idea what programs I've been working on to add value to this company,'' <PERSON> Smith </PERSON> said. `` But I think there are significant opportunities to improve the value.'' Some analysts have said <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION> shareholders might have a hard time rejecting the all-cash offer. Before Grand Met offered $ 60 a share, the stock was trading in the range of $ 39. <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION>'s stock closed down 25 cents to $ 57.87 -LCB- Thursday on the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>. The <LOCATION> Michigan </LOCATION> court ruling stemmed from <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION>'s attempt to block Grand met by suing the company in 14 states on the grounds a takeover would violate `` tied-house'' statutes prohibiting liquor manufacturers from owning retail liquor outlets. The decision by Judge <PERSON> Frederick </PERSON> <PERSON> Zeim </PERSON> in <ORGANIZATION> Oakland </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> County </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Circuit </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> marked the second time that such a restraining order has withstood a challenge by Grand Met, said <PERSON> J