<HEAD>Production Goes Down This Week</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Only version planned.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce 235,248 cars and light trucks this week, down from last week's 238,733, <PERSON> Ward </PERSON>'s Automotive Reports said Friday This week's production is higher than the same week a year ago, in which 224,066 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade journal said. <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> automakers were scheduled to make 151,038 cars this week, compared with 156,445 a week ago and 146,972 in the same week in 1987. Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 84,210, compared with last week's 82,288 and last year's 77,094. Canadian automakers were to build 20,526 cars this week, down from 20,787 a week ago and up from last year's 16,535. Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 19,496, compared with 20,225 a week ago and 18,025 in the same week last year.
