<HEAD>Irving Board Authorizes Bank of NY Merger</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: will be led with closing stock price.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Irving </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>'s board of directors approved Friday a management-backed $ 1.48 billion merger with hostile suitor <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, ending one of the nation's lengthiest and most bitter takeover battles. The merger will nearly double <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION>'s size, vaulting it close to the top 10 of the nation's largest banking companies. The two had a combined $ 47.8 billion in assets as of June 30. The board vote Friday came two days after Irving Chairman <PERSON> Joseph </PERSON> A. <PERSON> Rice </PERSON> announced he would abandon his year-long resistance to the proposed acquisition and drop all pending lawsuits and anti-takeover defenses aimed at stopping Bank of <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Rice </PERSON> also promised to move up his retirement plans and leave after the deal was completed. In return, <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> sweetened its previous hostile offer by about $ 200 million by slightly increasing the stock portion of the bid and adding stock warrants. <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> has a tender offer, scheduled to expire Oct. 21, under way for <PERSON> Irving </PERSON> shares. As of Sept. 30, nearly 10.46 million of Irving's 18.9 million outstanding shares had been tendered to <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION>, said <PERS