<HEAD>IC Files with SEC to Spin Off Illinois Central Railroad</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> IC </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Industries </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> on Friday filed a registration statement with the <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION> required for the spinoff of the Illinois Central Railroad. The parent company said it expects to distribute approximately 21 million shares of <ORGANIZATION> Illinois </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Central </ORGANIZATION> common stock to shareholders by the end of the year, after a favorable ruling by the <ORGANIZATION> Interstate </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commerce </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION> last week. Under the proposed plan, <ORGANIZATION> IC </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Industries </ORGANIZATION> shareholders willl receive one share of <ORGANIZATION> Illinois </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Central </ORGANIZATION> common stock for each five shares of <ORGANIZATION> IC </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Industries </ORGANIZATION> common stock they hold. Application is being made to have the new <ORGANIZATION> Illinois </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Central </ORGANIZATION> common stock listed on the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, IC said in a statement. <ORGANIZATION> IC </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Industries </ORGANIZATION> had earlier obtained a ruling from the <ORGANIZATION> Internal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Revenue </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> that the stock dividend will be tax-free to its shareholders. Before the distribution, <ORGANIZATION> IC </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Industries </ORGANIZATION> will contribute to the railroad $ 180 million in cash and forgiveness of net advances, plus $ 25 million in real estate. The parent company has been in the process of spinning off the railroad to its shareholders since early this year. With the spinoff of the railroad, <ORGANIZATION> IC </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Industries </ORGANIZATION> will change its name to <ORGANIZATION> Whitman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, as previously announced, effective Dec. 1. Its primary operating companies will then be <ORGANIZATION> Pet </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, a specialty foods company; <ORGANIZATION> Pepsi-Cola </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bottlers </ORGANIZATION>; muffler specialist <ORGANIZATION> Midas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>; and <ORGANIZATION> Hussman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, a manufacturer of food-service equipment.
