a half dollar to hit a new low of 75 cents a share Tuesday, but bounced back to $ 1.12 -LCB- on Wednesday and Thursday. Friday's announcement pushed it down to 87 -LCB- cents. The request to be filed with the <ORGANIZATION> FDIC </ORGANIZATION> will suggest that <ORGANIZATION> MCorp </ORGANIZATION> raise new capital from private investors, including current stockholders, to accompany the <ORGANIZATION> FDIC </ORGANIZATION> assistance, the statement said. `` MCorp continues to maintain adequate funding to meet the needs of its customers even though the recent economic challenges in our region have put enormous pressures on our situation,'' <PERSON> Bishop </PERSON> said. `` We believe that an early resolution by the <ORGANIZATION> FDIC </ORGANIZATION> of our assistance proposal will be the most cost-effective alternative for the <ORGANIZATION> FDIC </ORGANIZATION>.'' <ORGANIZATION> MCorp </ORGANIZATION> has 26 banks and 86 banking offices throughout the state. The company had assets of $ 20.1 billion as of June 30. Total deposits were $ 16.1 billion and total loans were $ 12.2 billion _ 36 percent of that in real estate loans. It was the only major <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> bank not to have resorted to a federal bailout or purchase by an out-of-state banking company. Earlier this year, Dallas-based <ORGANIZATION> First </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> RepublicBank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, the state's largest bank-holding company, sought federal assistance and ultimately was acquired by <ORGANIZATION> NCNB </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Charlotte </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.C. </LOCATION> Houston-based <ORGANIZATION> First </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> City </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bancorporation </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> was rescued by the <ORGANIZATION> FDIC </ORGANIZATION> and <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION> banker <PERSON> A. </PERSON> <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Abb